data.text:
The big weather story is a large low creating northerly winds off the lake. The lake effect snow machine has turned on and some heavy snow is expected for the snow belt of the south shore. Lake Effect Snow is expected to develop this evening, and then continue overnight and into Monday. Several inches of snowfall is expected for parts of Iron County!

Breezy North winds will produce some blowing and drifting snow. Travel conditions to become slick and hazardous for the Monday morning commute, mainly for northern Iron County! A Winter Storm Warning is in effect for Iron County Wisconsin, and a Winter Weather Advisory is in effect for Ashland County tonight and Monday.
